To deliver a fair verdict in a {CR_TRI_C}trial{##}, the jury evaluates the {CR_EVI_C}evidence{##} and {S_RHE_C}arguments{##} from both sides.
Still, partiality and {CHAR_STA_C}opinion{##} may sway their judgment. 

In case of a tie, position {icon_01} has the deciding vote. If vacant, position {icon_02} decides. If all members are absent, the accused is {CR_TRIPUN_C}absolved{##}.

The jury consists of:
 {icon_01} {O_JUD}
 {icon_02} {O_INQ}
 {icon_03} {O_PRE}

If any of these positions are vacant, a substitute juror will be assigned.

